'''''Seeing Anthropology: Cultural Anthropology Through Film''''' by [[Karl G. Heider]] introduces [[cultural anthropology]] with the use of both text and [[audiovisual|audiovisual media]]. First published in 1997, the work uses the tools of the [[ethnographic film]] discipline to inform its audience of the various cultural anthropology topics. Also, the text covers 14 different [[culture]]s in 17 chapters, which are also represented in 21 different short film clips ranging from two to twelve minutes.<ref name=ehren> {{cite journal | doi=10.1525/aa.1998.100.3.779 | jstor= 682068 | title=Seeing Anthropology: Cultural Anthropology through Film:Seeing Anthropology: Cultural Anthropology through Film | year=1998 | last1=Ehrenreich | first1=Jeffrey David | journal=[[American Anthropologist]] | volume=100 | issue=3 | pages=779 }}</ref><ref name=pearson> {{cite journal | last =Pearson | first =Sarah | title =Seeing Anthropology: Cultural Anthropology Through Film by Karl G Heider | journal =The Journal of the Polynesian Society | volume = 109 | issue = 3 | pages =320–322 | publisher = | location = Auckland, Australia | date = September 2000 | language = | jstor =20706939 | doi = }}</ref><ref name=higgins> {{cite journal |doi=10.1525/aeq.1998.29.3.385 |jstor =3196206 |title=Seeing Anthropology: Cultural Anthropology through Film |year=1998 |last1=Higgins |first1=Patricia J. |journal=Anthropology & Education Quarterly |volume=29 |issue=3 |pages=385}}</ref>
